# Frontend Linting & Formatting Rule

## 1. ESLint Configuration

- Use strict ESLint rules for TypeScript/React
- No unused variables or imports
- Consistent naming conventions (camelCase, PascalCase)

## 2. Prettier Formatting

- Automatic code formatting on save
- Consistent indentation and line breaks
- Trailing commas and semicolons

## 3. Pre-commit Hooks

- Husky for git hooks
- Lint-staged for incremental checks
- Block commits with linting errors

## 4. TypeScript Strict Mode

- Enable all strict mode flags
- No implicit any or undefined returns
- Proper null checking
